description:
In the 17th century, the Waldenses went through one of the worst episodes of their history. In this episode, we take you on this journey. The Massacre at Mount Castelluzzo was awfully gruesome, and now Mount Castelluzzo towers over the valley and town of Torre Pellicle as a constant reminder of the persecution that the Waldenses went through. They made the ultimate sacrifice for the cause of truth.

To find out more information about the Waldenses, check out our extended article.
